Class Order

Object
Order
public final class Order extends Object
Immutable entity class representing an Order, which is a collection of Article items purchased by a Customer.
An immutable class does not allow changes to attributes. DataFactory is the only class that creates Order objects from validated arguments.
Version:
"D12-1.0.0-SNAPSHOT"
Author:
"sgraupner"

  • Constructor Details

    • Order

      protected Order(long id, Customer customer, Pricing pricing, LocalDateTime created)
      None-public constructor used by DataFactory avoiding object creation outside the package.
      Parameters:
      id - order identifier supplied by DataFactory
      customer - reference to owning customer (must not be null)
      pricing - reference to pricing (country, currency, tax rates) that applies to order (must not be null)
      created - day and time (in UTC) when order was created (must not be null)
      Throws:
      IllegalArgumentException - if id is negative, arguments are null or creation date is outside bounds between "Jan 01, 2020 00:00" and "Dec 31, 2099 23:59"

      public void deleteItem(int i)

    • deleteItems

      public void deleteItems(Iterable<Integer> indices)
      Bulk delete of line items provided by a collection of indices. Only line items with i >= 0 and i < itemsCount() are deleted. Method has no effect for i outside valid bounds.
      Parameters:
      indices - collection of indices of line items to delete from order
